TITLE: Massachusetts man accused of stabbing wife to death
SUMMARY: Massachusetts police responded to a call over the weekend after a tenant saw blood on the stairway of their building. A woman was taken to the hospital where she was pronounced dead.

TITLE: NYC judge drops murder charge against bodega worker after Manhattan DA backtracks
SUMMARY: A New York City judge dismissed a murder charge for bodega worker Jose Alba after Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg's office said it couldn't prove against self-defense claims.

TITLE: Alabama football players made over $3 million in NIL money last year, Nick Saban says
SUMMARY: Alabama head coach Nick Saban spoke at SEC Media Days, telling reporters that his players made over $3 million in Name, Image, and Likeness money last year.

TITLE: Former de Blasio campaign aide Lis Smith slams 'gross,' ‘unshowered’ former mayor during MSNBC show
SUMMARY: Former Buttigieg 2020 advisor Lis Smith spoke to MSNBC host Nicolle Wallace on Monday about her new book in which she slammed former New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio.

TITLE: Georgia driver rams patrol cars during traffic stop in wild dashcam video
SUMMARY: A reckless driver hit a police officer, two witnesses and multiple patrol cars while fleeing a traffic stop in Byron, Georgia, on Friday, authorities said.

TITLE: Washington superintendent to resign following investigation, will receive $400K
SUMMARY: A superintendent northeast of Seattle is resigning after an investigation proved that he created a toxic work environment. He will receive $400,000.

TITLE: Cubs draft 12-time All-Star Mark McGwire's son Mason McGwire
SUMMARY: Mason McGwire is a pitcher out of Capistrano Valley High School in California while Mark McGwire was a massive slugger who was a 12-time All-Star.

TITLE: Rep. Waltz says China 'buying up' American land, resources: This is an 'economic war'
SUMMARY: Rep. Michael Waltz, R-Fla., responds to growing concern over China's economic advancement and control over land and resources in America and calls for action from Congress.

TITLE: Voters head to polls in Maryland, where Trump’s clout over GOP faces a test in gubernatorial primary
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump isn’t on the ballot on Tuesday in Maryland’s primaries, but the candidate he's backing is one of the co-front-runners in the GOP gubernatorial race

TITLE: UEFA Women's Championship: Belgium upsets Italy, moves on to quarterfinals
SUMMARY: In their upset win over Italy, Belgium moves on to play in the quarterfinals for the first time ever while eliminating Iceland in the process.

TITLE: Kristin Smart California trial: Paul Flores', father's attorneys try to poke holes in decades-old murder case
SUMMARY: Opening statements continue on Tuesday in the trial involving Paul Flores, the man accused of killing college student Kristin Smart in 1996, and his father, Ruben Flores.

TITLE: Larry Elder calls out Squad member's private security spending: A long line of 'left-wing hypocrites'
SUMMARY: Larry Elder slammed Squad member Cori Bush as a 'left-wing hypocrite' after she spent nearly $400k on private security amid the left's defund the police push

TITLE: Greg Sankey leaves door open to additional expansion, and more during SEC Media Day
SUMMARY: The SEC and Big Ten are currently the two powerhouse conferences in college football and both of the conferences still seek to expand.

TITLE: MLB All-Star Game: Jackie Robinson's legacy present during festivities
SUMMARY: As the All-Star break festivities go on in Los Angeles Jackie Robinson's legacy on MLB and sports as a whole are still felt today.

TITLE: Chris Sale has surgery, Red Sox yet to give timetable for return
SUMMARY: Red Sox announce Chris Sale had a successful surgery on his left pinky finger, his timetable to return for the season is to be determined.

TITLE: Ohio Senate showdown: New Ryan ad accuses Vance of using opioid non-profit to further ‘political career’
SUMMARY: A new TV ad by Ohio Democratic nominee Rep. Tim Ryan targets rival J.D. Vance over a non-profit organization the now-Republican nominee set up five years ago

TITLE: North Carolina's Pete Nance looks to fill role in national championship defense
SUMMARY: Pete Nance transfers from Northwestern looks to fill role with the North Carolina Tar Heels as they gear up for their National Championship defense.

TITLE: Meghan Markle, Prince Harry enjoy a date night in NYC after UN appearance
SUMMARY: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle had a busy Monday in New York City, giving a keynote address at the UN and a date night. Markle was also spotted with journalist Gloria Steinem.

TITLE: Parkland school shooting trial: 'Things are about to get bad,' gunman warns student
SUMMARY: A Parkland high school shooting survivor recalled running into Nikolas Cruz moments before the gunman slaughtered 17 people in the 2018 Florida mass murder.

TITLE: Oregon man to serve at least 50 years after killing grandparents
SUMMARY: Nicholas Borden-Cortez was sentenced to at least 50 years in prison for killing his grandparents. He was sentenced for two counts of first-degree murder.
